df = read.csv("fashion-mnist_train.csv")
# separate images and labels
ims = df[,-1]
labels = df[,1]
# randomly select some rows
train_inds = sample(1:nrow(ims), 2000, FALSE)
ims = ims[train_inds,]
labels = labels[train_inds]
# make the t-sne model
library(Rtsne)
tsne = Rtsne(ims, dims=2, perplexity=30, max_iter=10000, theta=0.05, initial_dims=50)
# get a set of distinctive colors for color-coding the observatoins

# number of unique colors
n = 10
# get 10 distinct colors for plot
qual_col_pals = brewer.pal.info[brewer.pal.info$category == 'qual',]
col_vector = unlist(mapply(brewer.pal, qual_col_pals$maxcolors, rownames(qual_col_pals)))
